Using `re.sub` with a callback function:

    inp = &quot;abcde.dhsjd.djshdj.(2019).(14856p).abdjskf&quot;
    def cb(m):
        return m.group(1).replace(&#39;.&#39;, &#39; &#39;) + m.group(2)

    output = re.sub(&#39;^(.*?)\((\d+)\).*$&#39;, cb, inp)
    print(output)

This prints:

    abcde dhsjd djshdj 2019

The strategy here is to match the first dot separated portion and year in two separate capture groups.  Then, inside the callback function we replace dot with space and concatenate together.

